          <descriptionSet>
               <display>Vibrant artwork featuring three yellow figures with pink crosses over their bodies, each covering their eyes, ears, and mouth respectively, against a bright orange background with radiating lines. Above, the text "IGNORANCE = FEAR" in blue, and below, "SILENCE = DEATH" alongside "FIGHT AIDS ACT UP" with a pink triangle. The style is reminiscent of Keith Haring's work.</display>
               <description source="Whitney Museum of American Art, New York">Vibrant artwork featuring three yellow figures with pink crosses over their bodies, each covering their eyes, ears, and mouth respectively, against a bright orange background with radiating lines. Above, the text "IGNORANCE = FEAR" in blue, and below, "SILENCE = DEATH" alongside "FIGHT AIDS ACT UP" with a pink triangle. The style is reminiscent of Keith Haring's work.</description>
          </descriptionSet>
          
